{"cursor":"8325","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn the United States, 'removal jurisdiction' refers to the right of a defendant\nto move a lawsuit filed in state court to the federal district court for the\nfederal judicial district in which the state court sits. This is a general\nexception to the usual American rule giving the plaintiff the right to make the\ndecision on the proper forum. Removal occurs when a defendant files a \"notice of\nremoval\" in the state court where the lawsuit is presently filed and the federal\ncourt which the defendant would like to remove the case to.\n","linknr":162,"url":"Removal_jurisdiction","recorded":1362534960,"links":12,"instances":["court_procedure","united_states","law"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Civil procedure","Jurisdiction"],"headings":["Removal jurisdiction","Timeliness of removal","Other issues","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Seal_of_the_United_States_Supreme_Court.svg/125px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Supreme_Court.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["state_court","united_states"],["remand","court_procedure"],["objection","law"],["remand","court_procedure"],["remand","court_procedure"]],"members":["remand","state_court","objection"],"related":["United_States","Defendant","Lawsuit","State_court_(United_States)","United_States_district_court","Plaintiff","Statute","Subject-matter_jurisdiction","Diversity_jurisdiction","Federal_question_jurisdiction","Diversity_jurisdiction","Class_action","Class_Action_Fairness_Act_of_2005","Founding_Fathers_of_the_United_States","Federalist_No._80","Remand_(court_procedure)","Circuit_split","Counterclaim","Workers'_compensation","Federal_Employers_Liability_Act","Ruby_Ridge","Supplemental_jurisdiction","Discretion","Objection_(law)","Remand_(court_procedure)","Remand_(court_procedure)","Class_Action_Fairness_Act_of_2005"]}